name: Chatty Cathy Coffee & Juice Press
reviews: Cute little spot in collegetown. We're talking tiny, but more cozy than cramped and it actually works for the type of place it is.
I feel like açaí bowls are a rare commodity in upstate NY, so I always enjoy going to places that serve them.
I had never tried one before this place so it was nice to try something new. I recommend if you are looking for something new.
The coffee was terrible in my case. Probably not all the stuff knows how to prepare an espresso drink.
